      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The government is prioritizing the long-term health and environmental stability of the nation, which is a fundamental societal good that outweighs short-term business convenience. While the immediate financial strain on small shops is real, the regulatory framework is designed to push the entire economy toward cleaner, more efficient practices. Any argument that economic fallout justifies ignoring critical climate targets is simply a short-sighted, anti-progress stance.",
      "source": "target",
