      "content": "calling it \"anti-progress\" feels pretty dismissive of people actually trying to run a livelihood. if the math doesn't add up for the people on the ground, isn't that a failure of the policy itself? how can you say it's a \"societal good\" if it's actively destroying local manufacturing communities?",
